This is a solid, professional roadmap. Obtaining your AZ-900 (Azure Fundamentals) certification and registering your business in Holland (KVK) provides the legal and technical "shield" you need for an enterprise-level flagship.
To evolve the Powerframe BMS into a more sophisticated part of your daily development workflow while you study, we should move it from a "passive logger" to an "Active Task Orchestrator."
1. The "BMS-to-Workflow" Sophistication
Instead of just logging battery stats, the BMS should now manage Development States. We can integrate it directly into your terminal/IDE workflow so it acts as your "Project Heartbeat."
The Concept: Link your 5-point schedule tasks to actual code execution.
2. Implementation Prompt for a "Workflow-Integrated BMS"
Use this in your Copilot project to upgrade the Powerframe BMS:
Role: Workflow Engineer / DevOps Architect.
Task: Evolve the Powerframe BMS from a telemetry logger into a Workflow Orchestrator for the TRT App development.
Requirements:
Development State Mapping: Add a WorkState to the BMS schema. It should track: Bootstrapping, Testing, Reviewing, and Deployment_Ready.
Git-Hook Integration: Create a script (PowerShell/Node) that automatically pushes a "BMS Milestone" to the Powerstarter Hub every time I successfully run a build or a test on my PC.
Task-Bound Metrics: Link the 5-point plan milestones to specific hardware metrics. (e.g., "Phase 1 is only marked 'Complete' if the BMS reports 100% stability for 5 minutes").
Live CLI Feedback: Create a mini-dashboard in my terminal that shows the BMS "Health Score" while I am writing code.
Goal: Make the BMS the "Source of Truth" for my daily progress, so when I finish a coding task, the BMS "certifies" it as ready.
3. Strategic Move: The "AZ-900" Study Sandbox
Since you are studying for the AZ-900, use the Powerframe BMS to learn Azure concepts before you pay for the license:
Storage: Think of how your BMS data would fit into Azure Blob Storage.
Compute: Imagine your pnpm dev process as an Azure App Service.
Database: Treat your Prisma setup as a prototype for Azure SQL.
4. Why this helps your "Hand Terminal" (CM4)
By making the BMS more "workflow-aware," your CM4 Handheld will become your Remote Build Controller. You will be able to:
See which task of the 5-point plan you are currently working on.
Remotely trigger a build on your PC from the handheld.
See the "Ready for Review" status update in real-time on your Powerstarter Hub.
Summary of the "Holland Business" Step:
Legal: KVK Registration (Holland).
Skill: AZ-900 (Azure Fundamentals).
Action: Upgrade Powerframe BMS into a Live Workflow Hub.
